you're gonna come too fast.

254
00:59:03,273 --> 00:59:07,903
Do you see what I mean?
You're so stupid. I can't believe it.

255
00:59:08,113 --> 00:59:13,187
So why does Bugsy pay you?
What do you do for him?

256
00:59:14,393 --> 00:59:18,432
- I close an eye once in a while.
- Well, now you close an eye for us.

257
00:59:18,593 --> 00:59:21,665
Why? What are you kids up to?

258
00:59:25,353 --> 00:59:26,786
He'll tell you.

259
00:59:26,953 --> 00:59:31,310
Me, him, Cockeye and Patsy,
we're working together.

260
00:59:31,633 --> 00:59:32,986
Bugsy'll flatten you.

261
00:59:33,153 --> 00:59:36,350
Besides, I don't put up with no
trouble on my beat.

262
00:59:36,513 --> 00:59:40,426
You'll put up, and you'll shut up.
You hear nothing, and you see nothing.

263
00:59:40,593 --> 00:59:42,390
Just like you did for Bugsy.

264
00:59:42,553 --> 00:59:43,906
Shit!

265
00:59:44,113 --> 00:59:48,948
Don't get upset. That makes it worse.
It can happen the first time.

266
00:59:49,113 --> 00:59:53,743
- It's them two talking out there.
- Can't you see you're ruining the mood?

267
00:59:53,913 --> 00:59:55,790
We made our deal.

268
00:59:56,393 --> 00:59:59,908
- So take a walk.
- Come here, honey.

269
01:00:01,833 --> 01:00:05,508
- Feel good, <i>bubeleh?</i>
- He'll never get it up.

270
01:00:06,793 --> 01:00:12,151
Relax. Okay. Calm down, calm down.

271
01:00:16,353 --> 01:00:20,790
Okay. Okay, come here.

272
01:01:37,313 --> 01:01:39,031
I'm glad the baby's better.

273
01:01:39,313 --> 01:01:43,465
- Happy <i>Pesach,</i> Deborah.
- Happy <i>Pesach,</i> Becky.

274
01:01:49,233 --> 01:01:51,588
Hurry. We're gonna be late.

275
01:01:51,753 --> 01:01:54,472
- There's Deborah.
- Sorry. Mama needed help.

276
01:01:54,633 --> 01:01:59,309
Good girl. I just locked up,
and I'm giving you the keys.

277
01:02:11,713 --> 01:02:15,626
I thought I'd just practice
my dance routines. All right?

278
01:02:15,793 --> 01:02:19,183
Make sure you don't let the <i>goyim</i> in.

279
01:02:19,873 --> 01:02:23,388
- Okay, bye.
- See you later, Debbie. Bye.

280
01:03:32,993 --> 01:03:35,268
Get down off of there, roach.

281
01:03:35,433 --> 01:03:37,105
That record's just like Ex-Lax.

282
01:03:37,273 --> 01:03:40,868
Every time I put it on,
you have to go to the bathroom.

283
01:03:57,673 --> 01:03:59,186
What are you doing?

284
01:03:59,353 --> 01:04:02,106
- Give me a drink.
- We're closed.

285
01:04:02,273 --> 01:04:06,630
Nice people don't drink on <i>Pesach.</i>
They go to the synagogue.

286
01:04:06,793 --> 01:04:08,704
So, what are you doing here?

287
01:04:08,873 --> 01:04:11,512
Somebody's got to keep an eye
on the place.

288
01:04:11,673 --> 01:04:15,746
There are a lot of thieves out there.
One could get into your house.

289
01:04:15,913 --> 01:04:18,950
Especially if you leave the door open.

290
01:04:49,913 --> 01:04:50,948
You can pray here too.

291
01:04:53,871 --> 01:04:57,546
Here or in the synagogue,
to God it's the same difference.

292
01:04:59,071 --> 01:05:01,221
Come over here and sit down.

293
01:05:32,951 --> 01:05:35,704
"My beloved is white and ruddy.

294
01:05:35,871 --> 01:05:39,341
His skin is as the most fine gold.

295
01:05:39,511 --> 01:05:43,390
His cheeks are as a bed of spices."

296
01:05:46,031 --> 01:05:49,706
Even though he hasn't washed
since last December.

297
01:05:53,831 --> 01:05:56,629
"His eyes are as the eyes
of doves.

298
01:05:56,791 --> 01:05:59,385
His body is as bright ivory.

299
01:05:59,551 --> 01:06:03,305
His legs are as pillars of marble."

300
01:06:05,111 --> 01:06:07,864
In pants so dirty
they stand by themselves.

301
01:06:09,591 --> 01:06:12,663
"He is altogether lovable."

302
01:06:14,191 --> 01:06:16,625
But he'll always be a two-bit punk...

303
01:06:16,791 --> 01:06:21,501
...so he'll never be my beloved.
What a shame.

304
01:06:51,631 --> 01:06:53,349
Somebody's there.

305
01:07:05,431 --> 01:07:07,581
There ain't nobody.

306
01:07:13,511 --> 01:07:15,263
It's Max.

307
01:07:15,431 --> 01:07:17,865
So that's who it was.

308
01:07:18,511 --> 01:07:20,069
Noodles!

309
01:07:24,231 --> 01:07:26,791
Go on, run.
Your mother's calling you.

310
01:07:32,631 --> 01:07:33,950
Noodles!

311
01:07:35,111 --> 01:07:37,466
Just gonna go see what he wants.

312
01:08:10,951 --> 01:08:14,023
- You been here long?
- No.

313
01:08:15,071 --> 01:08:17,221
Were you in there?

314
01:08:19,511 --> 01:08:21,627
You're one lousy kisser.

315
01:08:21,791 --> 01:08:24,828
I seen you go in there
after that ball-buster.

316
01:08:24,991 --> 01:08:29,826
Here's the stuff from last night. We got
4 for the silverware, 6 for the typewriter.

317
01:08:30,031 --> 01:08:34,024
Lipschitz wouldn't cough up any more.
We gotta get somebody else.

318
01:08:36,271 --> 01:08:38,785
I came to divvy up.

319
01:08:39,231 --> 01:08:43,668
- Tomorrow, with the others.
- I also came to pick you up.

320
01:08:45,071 --> 01:08:48,950
- I can't come right now.
- The houses, the stores are all empty.

321
01:08:49,111 --> 01:08:52,899
We got our pick. You pick that.

322
01:08:53,071 --> 01:08:54,948
Yeah.

323
01:08:57,871 --> 01:09:02,183
Some partner I got. Have fun.

324
01:09:07,791 --> 01:09:09,827
How's it going, boys?

325
01:09:09,991 --> 01:09:12,061
Who's that?

326
01:09:12,431 --> 01:09:14,308
Bugsy.

327
01:09:30,871 --> 01:09:34,181
I hear you guys are in business
for yourselves now.

328
01:09:34,351 --> 01:09:37,388
I hear youse are doing real good.

329
01:09:43,151 --> 01:09:46,223
Ain't you gonna introduce me
to your friend here?

330
01:09:48,591 --> 01:09:51,025
I'll introduce myself.

331
01:09:55,751 --> 01:09:57,548
Excuse the glove.

332
01:10:06,911 --> 01:10:08,424
Son of a bitch!

333
01:10:53,911 --> 01:10:55,788
That's my cut.

334
01:10:56,111 --> 01:10:59,945
You don't work for me,
you don't work for no one.

335
01:11:00,111 --> 01:11:01,863
I don't like bosses.

336
01:11:02,271 --> 01:11:05,627
You was better off
you stayed in the Bronx.

337
01:11:08,751 --> 01:11:11,629
It would have been better for you too.

338
01:11:51,951 --> 01:11:55,944
- I'm gonna kill him one of these days.
- Yeah?

339
01:11:56,391 --> 01:12:00,669
Meantime it looks like he's killed us.

340
01:12:19,151 --> 01:12:21,870
Deborah, open up the door.

341
01:12:22,991 --> 01:12:25,869
Deborah, open up the door.

342
01:12:27,311 --> 01:12:28,869
Deborah.

343
01:13:09,191 --> 01:13:12,866
- That stuff, is it ready?
- We're loading it.

344
01:13:46,351 --> 01:13:50,583
- <i>Che cazzo succede</i> down here?
- Al, we got the big boys with us today.

345
01:13:50,751 --> 01:13:54,346
- They wanna work for us.
- Doing what Bugsy did. We want his job.

346
01:13:54,511 --> 01:13:55,626
Do you get that?

347
01:13:56,951 --> 01:14:00,910
We the best escorts you ever gonna get.

348
01:14:01,711 --> 01:14:05,624
<i>A fangulo a ma,</i> escort your
mother's ass out of here.

349
01:14:05,791 --> 01:14:10,819
Okay. Let's go, Noodles. We'll peddle
your invention somewhere else.

350
01:14:12,511 --> 01:14:14,502
Hey, wait a minute.

351
01:14:16,271 --> 01:14:17,260
What invention?

352
01:14:17,431 --> 01:14:20,264
- You ship your stuff by the river, right?
- Sometimes.

353
01:14:20,431 --> 01:14:23,821
And when you get caught,
you throw the cases overboard.

354
01:14:23,991 --> 01:14:26,630
- You lose the whole shipment.
- So?

355
01:14:26,791 --> 01:14:29,385
For 10 percent,
we'll save it all for you.

356
01:14:29,551 --> 01:14:32,748
- What do you got, a submarine?
- We got salt.

357
01:14:33,591 --> 01:14:35,070
You got what?

358
01:14:35,231 --> 01:14:39,907
- Me and the boys are rolling salts.
- We need 3 tons of salt per shipment.

359
01:14:40,071 --> 01:14:43,461
Get the fuck out of here.
Go back to school where you belong.

360
01:14:43,911 --> 01:14:46,266
What is it with all this salt?

361
01:14:46,431 --> 01:14:50,788
Hey, hey, we got salt on our noodles.
Show 'em.

362
01:15:02,991 --> 01:15:04,709
This is full of salt.

363
01:15:09,671 --> 01:15:11,184
All right, come here.

364
01:15:25,711 --> 01:15:28,271
- So?
- Keep your shirt on.

365
01:15:28,431 --> 01:15:30,945
We gotta wait for the salt
to dissolve.

366
01:16:01,831 --> 01:16:04,629
- Well?
- Hey, what's wrong?

367
01:16:10,511 --> 01:16:11,785
Hey, look.

368
01:16:12,511 --> 01:16:13,785
Wow!

369
01:16:15,911 --> 01:16:17,185
Great!

370
01:16:18,591 --> 01:16:20,980
- Look at that!
- It's great.

371
01:16:21,151 --> 01:16:22,504
- Noodles.
- Look.

372
01:16:24,111 --> 01:16:27,467
- I see 'em! What did I tell you?
- Yeah.

373
01:16:30,831 --> 01:16:32,059
Yeah!

374
01:16:41,791 --> 01:16:44,828
- Hooray.
- Hooray for us!

375
01:16:48,591 --> 01:16:49,785
We did it.

376
01:16:50,911 --> 01:16:52,310
Come here, Max.

377
01:16:53,751 --> 01:16:56,902
- We did it.
- No, Max, no!

378
01:17:00,511 --> 01:17:01,705
Max.

379
01:17:03,311 --> 01:17:04,664
Max.

380
01:17:15,871 --> 01:17:17,145
Max!

381
01:17:19,631 --> 01:17:20,825
Max!

382
01:17:34,671 --> 01:17:36,901
What would you do without me?

383
01:18:39,831 --> 01:18:41,059
There.

384
01:18:44,271 --> 01:18:47,422
From here on, we establish the
shared funds of the gang.

385
01:18:47,591 --> 01:18:50,424
They belong to all of us together
and to none of us alone.

386
01:18:50,591 --> 01:18:55,745
And we solemnly swear to put in 50
percent of everything we make. Agreed?

387
01:18:55,911 --> 01:18:57,060
Agreed.

388
01:18:57,391 --> 01:18:59,063
- Agreed.
- Agreed.

389
01:19:02,111 --> 01:19:03,305
Agreed.

390
01:19:05,711 --> 01:19:07,542
I wanna take another peek.

391
01:19:26,471 --> 01:19:28,223
Announcing the departure of...

392
01:19:28,391 --> 01:19:32,862
...the Lackawanna Railroad,
Hudson Valley Express, Poughkeepsie...

393
01:19:33,031 --> 01:19:37,741
...AIbany, Utica, and Buffalo.

394
01:19:39,151 --> 01:19:40,425
All aboard.

395
01:19:44,511 --> 01:19:48,026
This goes to Fat Moe.
We don't tell him what it's for.

396
01:19:48,191 --> 01:19:51,422
And he gives it back
only when we're all together.

397
01:19:51,591 --> 01:19:52,740
Agreed?

398
01:19:53,791 --> 01:19:54,985
Agreed.

399
01:19:58,711 --> 01:20:00,064
Agreed.

400
01:20:55,311 --> 01:20:57,222
Bugsy's coming! Run!

401
01:21:46,871 --> 01:21:48,145
Noodles.

402
01:21:49,631 --> 01:21:51,622
I slipped.

403
01:23:29,991 --> 01:23:31,185
Schmuck.

404
01:25:40,671 --> 01:25:42,184
Wanna go in?

405
01:25:45,991 --> 01:25:47,310
Yeah.

406
01:25:47,751 --> 01:25:49,070
You a relative?

407
01:25:52,751 --> 01:25:53,945
An uncle.

408
01:26:06,031 --> 01:26:07,305
It's open.

409
01:29:11,471 --> 01:29:14,781
"Erected to their everlasting memory
by their friend and brother...

410
01:29:14,951 --> 01:29:17,226
...David Aaronson, 1967."

411
01:31:50,551 --> 01:31:52,701
Can I take that for you, sir?

412
01:31:55,031 --> 01:31:56,987
Your limousine is waiting.

413
01:32:06,991 --> 01:32:08,265
Maxie.

414
01:32:19,751 --> 01:32:22,584
How are you, uncle?
You're looking good.

415
01:32:23,991 --> 01:32:25,709
You're looking a little better.

416
01:32:29,111 --> 01:32:32,899
Come on. Better get
you off the streets.

417
01:32:35,991 --> 01:32:39,142
- Some limousine.
- What are you talking, huh?

418
01:32:39,471 --> 01:32:43,828
We own the company now.
It's a good cover. It pays off too.

419
01:32:43,991 --> 01:32:47,700
My mother wrote me you was in the
body-snatching business.

420
01:32:49,951 --> 01:32:53,068
I appreciate everything you did
for my family.

421
01:32:53,271 --> 01:32:55,421
Forget it. It's your dough.

422
01:32:56,031 --> 01:32:59,262
It's all down in black and white
in the company books.

423
01:33:00,031 --> 01:33:05,264
You're the company. You and Patsy and
Cockeye. Gravediggers and partners.

424
01:33:05,431 --> 01:33:08,423
Hey, enough of this.
Business before pleasure.

425
01:33:09,231 --> 01:33:11,222
We got a rush job. Here.

426
01:33:13,991 --> 01:33:16,664
Come here. Look at this. Come here.

427
01:33:18,471 --> 01:33:22,020
Sudden death. Fucking tragedy, huh?

428
01:33:23,311 --> 01:33:26,508
- 26 years old.
- 26?

429
01:33:28,351 --> 01:33:32,264
- What a shame.
- Great stiff. She died of an overdose.

430
01:33:32,431 --> 01:33:34,342
And I'm ready for another.

431
01:33:34,511 --> 01:33:37,867
Pump the life into her.
You didn't turn pansy in there, did you?

432
01:33:41,431 --> 01:33:42,830
There you go.

433
01:33:45,671 --> 01:33:49,550
Turning over in the grave.
They do it every time.

434
01:34:29,191 --> 01:34:32,740
Don't worry. A pansy he ain't.

435
01:34:34,471 --> 01:34:36,826
- Thanks.
- You're welcome, Noodles.

436
01:34:37,471 --> 01:34:39,189
Whoops. Sorry.

437
01:34:39,511 --> 01:34:41,581
Thanks. Good night.

438
01:34:42,271 --> 01:34:48,107
- Hey, you want a little pick-me-up?
- No, thanks. I've had mine.

439
01:34:48,671 --> 01:34:52,584
- Did you give her your all?
- What do you think? You bet I did.

440
01:35:16,271 --> 01:35:19,024
Wait till you see this place.

441
01:35:19,191 --> 01:35:20,590
It's over here.

442
01:35:22,791 --> 01:35:26,261
- Where we going?
- To a place that never closes.

443
01:35:27,151 --> 01:35:29,062
Whoops. Watch yourself.

444
01:35:45,831 --> 01:35:46,820
What's this?

445
01:35:46,991 --> 01:35:49,380
Our place.
We got the hottest spot in town.

446
01:35:57,151 --> 01:35:59,585
This is the real Fat Moe's.

447
01:36:00,911 --> 01:36:02,788
Get rid of that rag, will you?

448
01:36:04,031 --> 01:36:06,340
- What do you think?
- It's beautiful.

449
01:36:06,511 --> 01:36:08,741
- You like it?
- Beautiful. Beautiful.

450
01:36:23,551 --> 01:36:25,269
Hey, give me that.

451
01:36:30,311 --> 01:36:33,383
- Noodles. Look who's here.
- Patsy, look.

452
01:36:33,551 --> 01:36:37,021
Come here, son of a bitch.
Come here! Come here!

453
01:36:38,311 --> 01:36:40,506
- You look fantastic.
- Wait a minute.

454
01:36:40,671 --> 01:36:41,990
How you doing?

455
01:36:44,751 --> 01:36:46,867
- Look how big you got.
- Me?

456
01:36:47,031 --> 01:36:48,987
Noodles. Oh, God.

457
01:36:49,791 --> 01:36:52,430
- Noodles!
- Number three coming through.

458
01:36:57,751 --> 01:37:00,106
Let's have a toast, for chrissakes!

459
01:37:00,271 --> 01:37:02,785
- You look like shit.
- I just got out of prison.

460
01:37:02,951 --> 01:37:06,023
- Nice guy.
- Hey, Noodles, get a load of this.

461
01:37:09,031 --> 01:37:10,908
Hey, scotch heating.

462
01:37:11,071 --> 01:37:12,982
Yeah, a buck a cup.

463
01:37:14,071 --> 01:37:15,470
- A buck a cup?
- Yeah.

464
01:37:15,631 --> 01:37:17,747
- How much it cost us?
- Costing us?

465
01:37:17,911 --> 01:37:20,186
A dime, including overhead.

466
01:37:20,391 --> 01:37:23,588
- Hey, Noodles.
- Fat Moe.

467
01:37:29,351 --> 01:37:30,830
You look terrific.

468
01:37:33,551 --> 01:37:38,341
- Look like you lost an ounce or two.
- You think I'm gonna lose hemorrhoids.

469
01:37:38,591 --> 01:37:40,946
Can't recognize him without an apron.

470
01:37:41,111 --> 01:37:42,942
<i>- L 'Chaim.</i>
<i>- L 'Chaim.</i>

471
01:37:44,231 --> 01:37:45,425
Welcome home.

472
01:37:49,231 --> 01:37:53,144
What kind of maître d' are you?
You don't even show a guy around.

473
01:37:53,311 --> 01:37:54,903
- Yeah.
- What's with you?

474
01:37:55,071 --> 01:37:58,825
- I didn't know. I'm sorry.
- You're some bunch of <i>shtunks.</i>

475
01:37:58,991 --> 01:38:01,983
- You don't come up and get me.
- He's the <i>shtunk.</i>

476
01:38:02,151 --> 01:38:07,145
- He said you weren't out till Monday.
- You get him the next time he gets out.

477
01:38:08,031 --> 01:38:09,862
God forbid. God forbid.

478
01:38:27,071 --> 01:38:30,222
Come on, let's see if you can
guess who it is.

479
01:38:35,151 --> 01:38:39,269
Charlotte russe. With a little too
much whipped cream.

480
01:38:40,551 --> 01:38:41,984
Peggy.

481
01:38:46,031 --> 01:38:50,104
Hey, you watch it, now.
And my prices, they've gone up.

482
01:38:50,271 --> 01:38:55,140
I work in a high-class joint now.
And I get paid by the pound.

483
01:38:55,711 --> 01:38:59,863
My Peggy, she's worth every penny
of it too, my red-hot mama.

484
01:39:01,711 --> 01:39:03,429
Come on, come on.

485
01:39:05,791 --> 01:39:07,190
Timber!

486
01:39:08,271 --> 01:39:12,184
You've seen your old pals,
now I want you to meet some new ones.

487
01:39:12,351 --> 01:39:16,981
- I'll see you later.
- You gonna lay here all night or what?

488
01:39:25,951 --> 01:39:29,739
Cockeye wanted to play with the band.
I'm serious.

489
01:39:36,311 --> 01:39:37,539
Come on.

490
01:40:03,551 --> 01:40:06,861
- Aren't you going to say hello?
- Hello.

491
01:40:25,951 --> 01:40:29,739
- Your brother's a real friend.
- He's a romantic.

492
01:40:40,671 --> 01:40:44,380
- Max tell you I was getting out today?
- Max? No.

493
01:40:45,111 --> 01:40:49,502
- You remembered yourself?
- No, Moe. It's always Moe.

494
01:40:54,151 --> 01:40:55,425
Yeah.

495
01:41:04,111 --> 01:41:06,147
You weren't counting the days?

496
01:41:06,311 --> 01:41:11,544
Of course I was. 4344, 4343.

