There's a difference.

1206
03:06:34,764 --> 03:06:37,597
At least you recognized me,
that's something.

1207
03:06:37,764 --> 03:06:40,642
Actresses have good memories.

1208
03:06:50,004 --> 03:06:52,234
You want a drink?

1209
03:06:56,284 --> 03:06:58,593
I'm having one.

1210
03:07:08,604 --> 03:07:09,593
Margo.

1211
03:07:11,284 --> 03:07:13,878
- Yes, miss?
- That's all for now. You can go.

1212
03:07:14,044 --> 03:07:16,160
All right, miss.

1213
03:07:20,844 --> 03:07:23,597
She called you "miss."

1214
03:07:23,924 --> 03:07:26,233
You never got married?

1215
03:07:27,044 --> 03:07:28,602
No.

1216
03:07:32,044 --> 03:07:33,523
You live alone?

1217
03:07:41,324 --> 03:07:42,757
No.

1218
03:07:49,324 --> 03:07:51,554
Where were you?

1219
03:07:54,364 --> 03:07:56,673
I was out of town.

1220
03:07:59,404 --> 03:08:02,077
Have you been back long?

1221
03:08:03,004 --> 03:08:05,313
A couple of days.

1222
03:08:05,484 --> 03:08:07,634
Are you staying?

1223
03:08:18,804 --> 03:08:20,157
That depends.

1224
03:08:22,964 --> 03:08:24,955
Why do you want to see me?

1225
03:08:26,724 --> 03:08:28,954
Two reasons.

1226
03:08:29,124 --> 03:08:34,403
Wanted to see if you did the right thing,
turning me down to become an actress.

1227
03:08:38,404 --> 03:08:39,917
Well?

1228
03:08:42,604 --> 03:08:44,913
You did. You're terrific.

1229
03:08:59,884 --> 03:09:02,842
"Age cannot wither her."

1230
03:09:03,044 --> 03:09:05,922
It's like the play
was written for you.

1231
03:09:09,244 --> 03:09:11,599
What was the other reason?

1232
03:09:11,804 --> 03:09:13,999
The other reason...

1233
03:09:17,084 --> 03:09:21,236
...is to decide whether I should go
to a party tomorrow night

1234
03:09:27,684 --> 03:09:29,163
Party?

1235
03:09:32,324 --> 03:09:34,713
Yeah, on Long Island.

1236
03:09:36,164 --> 03:09:39,201
A Secretary Bailey.

1237
03:09:42,884 --> 03:09:44,954
Do you know Secretary Bailey?

1238
03:09:46,724 --> 03:09:47,873
No.

1239
03:09:50,204 --> 03:09:52,434
But I was invited anyway.

1240
03:10:00,604 --> 03:10:03,357
If you don't know each other,
why were you invited?

1241
03:10:03,524 --> 03:10:05,003
I don't know.

1242
03:10:06,564 --> 03:10:08,520
I thought you might know why.

1243
03:10:09,524 --> 03:10:10,843
Me?

1244
03:10:11,044 --> 03:10:12,602
Why me?

1245
03:10:17,804 --> 03:10:19,795
Because you know him.

1246
03:10:20,564 --> 03:10:22,395
- Who is it?
- It's me, David.

1247
03:10:22,604 --> 03:10:25,164
- No, David.
- Can I come in?

1248
03:10:25,364 --> 03:10:28,083
No. Just wait outside, I'll call you.

1249
03:10:28,284 --> 03:10:30,559
Okay, I'll be right here.

1250
03:10:33,244 --> 03:10:36,873
- What does Bailey want from me?
- You came to ask me that?

1251
03:10:37,084 --> 03:10:39,917
- Why'd he send me an invitation?
- I don't know.

1252
03:10:40,124 --> 03:10:44,276
Why should I know about your
invitations? I don't know anything.

1253
03:10:44,484 --> 03:10:48,318
What do you want?
Why did you come here? I know nothing.

1254
03:10:48,484 --> 03:10:51,044
Now you're a lousy actress.

1255
03:10:53,764 --> 03:10:56,483
Who is Secretary Bailey?

1256
03:11:04,884 --> 03:11:08,354
Secretary Bailey is a rich businessman.

1257
03:11:13,844 --> 03:11:18,235
He came to the United States as
an immigrant and made a lot of money...

1258
03:11:18,444 --> 03:11:22,232
...in San Francisco and L.A.,
where he's lived for 30 years.

1259
03:11:22,404 --> 03:11:26,238
I know all that. It's all in the papers.
What else is there?

1260
03:11:32,484 --> 03:11:35,362
He married a very wealthy woman.

1261
03:11:36,604 --> 03:11:38,834
They had a child.

1262
03:11:39,204 --> 03:11:42,116
She died when the child was born.

1263
03:11:42,684 --> 03:11:47,041
A few years ago, he went into politics.
Moved here.

1264
03:11:47,204 --> 03:11:51,641
That's history. I'm not talking
about that. I'm talking about now.

1265
03:11:52,204 --> 03:11:54,718
Right now he's in trouble.

1266
03:11:56,324 --> 03:12:01,603
Just tell me you've been living with him
all these years, and you're his lover.

1267
03:12:10,084 --> 03:12:12,962
Age can wither me, Noodles.

1268
03:12:16,524 --> 03:12:19,038
We're both getting old.

1269
03:12:24,164 --> 03:12:27,315
All that we have left now
are our memories.

1270
03:12:30,124 --> 03:12:35,835
If you go to that party on Saturday
night, you won't have those anymore.

1271
03:12:37,164 --> 03:12:39,519
Tear up that invitation.

1272
03:12:41,804 --> 03:12:44,318
There's an exit back this way.

1273
03:12:45,204 --> 03:12:48,002
Noodles, go through it.

1274
03:12:50,564 --> 03:12:52,361
Keep walking.

1275
03:12:52,564 --> 03:12:54,714
Don't turn around.

1276
03:12:56,004 --> 03:12:58,040
Please, Noodles.

1277
03:12:58,244 --> 03:13:01,122
I'm begging you. Please.

1278
03:13:07,324 --> 03:13:10,714
Are you afraid that I'll turn
into a pillar of salt?

1279
03:13:14,084 --> 03:13:17,679
If you go out that door, yes.

1280
03:14:13,524 --> 03:14:16,357
This is Secretary Bailey's son.

1281
03:14:16,564 --> 03:14:19,920
His name's David, just like yours.

1282
03:17:04,444 --> 03:17:06,196
Please go in.

1283
03:17:20,004 --> 03:17:22,234
What are you waiting for?

1284
03:17:25,764 --> 03:17:28,324
I don't understand, Mr. Bailey.

1285
03:17:53,724 --> 03:17:55,715
Sit down, Noodles.

1286
03:17:59,804 --> 03:18:01,522
Make yourself comfortable.

1287
03:18:19,164 --> 03:18:21,758
I'm glad you accepted my invitation.

1288
03:18:21,924 --> 03:18:23,835
Well, I was curious.

1289
03:18:26,684 --> 03:18:29,676
So many important people in one place.

1290
03:18:29,884 --> 03:18:33,593
Yes. Well, the rats usually
desert a sinking ship.

1291
03:18:34,044 --> 03:18:37,798
But in my case, they appear to be
flocking onboard.

1292
03:18:48,964 --> 03:18:52,639
Yeah, well, I read about
your troubles in the newspapers.

1293
03:18:53,964 --> 03:18:58,435
But a man in your position, with all
your power and all your privileges...

1294
03:18:58,644 --> 03:19:02,717
...has to assume a certain amount
of responsibility...

1295
03:19:03,364 --> 03:19:05,719
...a certain amount of risk.

1296
03:19:12,884 --> 03:19:15,523
Why'd you ask me
to come here, Mr. Bailey?

1297
03:19:18,724 --> 03:19:23,036
That invitation doesn't mean
a goddamn thing, and you know it.

1298
03:19:23,404 --> 03:19:26,794
All that counts is what
was in that suitcase.

1299
03:19:28,404 --> 03:19:30,998
The money and the contract.

1300
03:19:33,724 --> 03:19:36,796
It didn't say who the contract
was on, though.

1301
03:19:38,084 --> 03:19:40,393
Haven't you figured that out yet?

1302
03:19:42,044 --> 03:19:43,523
You, Mr. Bailey?

1303
03:19:56,764 --> 03:20:00,313
I haven't had a gun in my hand
for many, many years.

1304
03:20:01,884 --> 03:20:07,197
My eyes aren't too good,
even with my glasses. My hands shake.

1305
03:20:09,964 --> 03:20:13,798
- And I wouldn't want to miss.
- Cut the bullshit, Noodles.

1306
03:20:15,284 --> 03:20:17,923
I'm already a dead man.

1307
03:20:18,804 --> 03:20:23,036
At least give me the chance
to settle the debt that I owe to you.

1308
03:20:23,684 --> 03:20:27,040
I'll never make it before
the investigating committee.

1309
03:20:27,204 --> 03:20:30,992
They're scared I'll implicate
the whole bunch of 'em.

1310
03:20:31,364 --> 03:20:33,480
They gotta get rid of me.

1311
03:20:36,044 --> 03:20:38,877
Today is as good a day as any.

1312
03:20:41,124 --> 03:20:43,240
You do it, Noodles.

1313
03:20:44,164 --> 03:20:47,395
You're the only person
I can accept it from.

1314
03:20:54,004 --> 03:20:56,472
You see, I found out where you were.

1315
03:20:56,644 --> 03:20:59,602
I brought you back here for this.

1316
03:21:00,884 --> 03:21:03,956
To even the score between you and me.

1317
03:21:06,244 --> 03:21:08,599
You can get out through there.

1318
03:21:15,564 --> 03:21:19,921
It leads right down to the street.
Nobody will see you.

1319
03:21:26,404 --> 03:21:30,602
I don't know what you're talking about.
You don't owe me a thing.

1320
03:21:38,244 --> 03:21:44,114
Your eyes were too full of tears to see
it wasn't me burned up on that street.

1321
03:21:44,924 --> 03:21:46,721
It was somebody else.

1322
03:21:48,244 --> 03:21:52,954
You were too shocked to realize
that the cops were in on it too.

1323
03:21:53,564 --> 03:21:56,636
That was a syndicate
operation, Noodles.

1324
03:22:06,524 --> 03:22:08,435
You're crazy.

1325
03:22:10,804 --> 03:22:14,877
You said that to me once before,
a long time ago.

1326
03:22:15,164 --> 03:22:18,474
My mind was never as clear
as it was at that moment.

1327
03:22:19,204 --> 03:22:22,560
I took away your whole life from you.

1328
03:22:22,764 --> 03:22:25,483
I've been living in your place.

1329
03:22:26,684 --> 03:22:29,152
I took everything.

1330
03:22:30,524 --> 03:22:32,594
I took your money.

1331
03:22:33,284 --> 03:22:35,320
I took your girl.

1332
03:22:36,004 --> 03:22:40,600
All I left for you was 35 years of grief
over having killed me.

1333
03:22:42,364 --> 03:22:44,082
Now, why don't you shoot?

1334
03:24:14,844 --> 03:24:17,642
It's true,
I have killed people, Mr. Bailey.

1335
03:24:17,844 --> 03:24:22,395
Sometimes to defend myself.
Sometimes for money.

1336
03:24:22,684 --> 03:24:25,118
And many people used to come to us.

1337
03:24:25,324 --> 03:24:28,122
Business partners, rivals...

1338
03:24:28,484 --> 03:24:30,554
...Iovers.

1339
03:24:30,924 --> 03:24:34,883
Some of the jobs we took,
and some we didn't.

1340
03:24:47,724 --> 03:24:50,557
Yours is one we would never touch.

1341
03:24:51,404 --> 03:24:54,237
Is this your way of getting revenge?

1342
03:24:58,044 --> 03:24:59,557
No.

1343
03:25:02,764 --> 03:25:05,756
It's just the way I see things.

1344
03:26:05,884 --> 03:26:08,557
It's 10:25...

1345
03:26:09,804 --> 03:26:12,841
...and I've got nothing left to lose.

1346
03:26:14,884 --> 03:26:18,672
When you've been betrayed by a friend,
you hit back.

1347
03:26:23,524 --> 03:26:25,276
Do it.

1348
03:26:46,524 --> 03:26:49,038
You see, Mr. Secretary...

1349
03:26:50,964 --> 03:26:52,955
...I have a story also.

1350
03:26:53,884 --> 03:26:56,318
A little simpler than yours.

1351
03:26:57,404 --> 03:27:01,920
Many years ago I had a friend,
a dear friend.

1352
03:27:03,484 --> 03:27:06,601
I turned him in to save his life...

1353
03:27:06,804 --> 03:27:08,999
...but he was killed.

1354
03:27:10,244 --> 03:27:12,963
But he wanted it that way.

1355
03:27:13,964 --> 03:27:16,080
It was a great friendship.

1356
03:27:19,044 --> 03:27:22,923
It went bad for him,
and it went bad for me too.

1357
03:27:27,684 --> 03:27:29,754
Good night, Mr. Bailey.

1358
03:27:38,564 --> 03:27:42,113
I hope the investigation
turns out to be nothing.

1359
03:27:43,964 --> 03:27:47,843
It'd be a shame to see
a lifetime of work go to waste.

1360
